commentTextItems.html: the tension's over and Pakistan have won! Junaid fired this one full on the off stump, Prasanna made room looking to scoop it over the off side but it dipped and landed safely on Sharjeel's palms at mid-off

commentPostTextItems.html: Mathews: "We witnessed a great match, esp the stand between Seekkuge and Sachitra, very pleasing to see how they fought. We knew that the dew would come into play so we were happy to chase. I thought it was still a pleasing performance so no need to panic."
Ali Inam: "Not sure if it's a post match presentation or a birthday party !!"
Hafeez is the Man of the Match: "It was much needed for me, Maqsood batted well, Sharjeel started well. I really wanted to do something in this game."
Misbah: "It was a much needed innings from Hafeez, Sharjeel a good prospect. We need to improve on the bowling and fielding, too many lapses. If the team is winning, I don't want to bat."
That's it from us here. Good start to the series. Join us for game 2 on Friday in Dubai. Thanks for your mails and company. Cheers!
End of match: Najam Sethi tweets: "Yaaaayyyyyy Team Pak wins again!!!!"

Pakistan win by 11 runs but make heavy weather of it. They were comfortably placed to win this comfortably but panic set in and a pair of attacking 40s from Prasanna and Senanayake really gave Sri Lanka hope. Pakistan just about made enough. Makes you wonder what could have been had at least one of Sanga, Chandimal or Mathews had carried on. Also, had Afridi bowled out his quota. Ask Misbah.
Dew may have been a factor. Will captains be more comfortable bowling first going forward?

Ali Wazir: "Although I'm a Pakistan fan, they way the Sri Lankans played, they deserved the victory a tad more than Pakistan. Congratulations to them for putting on such a great fight and a thrilling match!"
AB: "Pakistanis weren't playing to win, they were playing to not lose. There is a difference and that was apparent in this match!"

commentTextItems.html: Out of the stadium! Fetch that! This was bowled too full and was a slower ball too, stood at the crease and launched miles and miles over wide long-on

commentPostTextItems.html: Sharjeel Khan: "Junaid is the same bowler who bowl 6 yorkers in an over in South Africa but here they all are bowling short and juicy lengths."

commentTextItems.html: 6 + 4! The fuller length fails Bhatti, outside off and another 'hit me' ball, Prasanna backs away and scoops it over point nobody patrolling the deep

dismissalComment.html: Dilshan fails to get his placement right two balls in a row but this time he pays the price! Good field placement by the captain to have a deep square leg, it was short and Dilshan couldn't resist the pull, hits it flat and quick to Hafeez who takes a few paces back and takes the catch, falls over with the momentum

dismissalText.commentary: Kumar Sangakkara c †Umar Akmal b Shahid Afridi 23 (33b 0x4 0x6 47m) SR: 69.69

dismissalComment.html: Afridi's got the Big Fish! And he ditched his trademark 'X' celebration and instead took off with his arm outstretched. It was wide outside off and Sanga chased it, thick outside edge and Akmal fumbled and took it on the second attempt. Afridi's celebration was a bit unusual too
